message.content:
cs.NI, cs.GT, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.CE

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with infrastructure sharing among mobile network operators and analyzes the coverage probability and power consumption of the network. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is also likely as the paper formulates the pricing and fraction of infrastructure to be sold using a Cournot oligopoly game. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is another possible category as the paper analyzes the trade-off between increasing the transmit power of a base station and the base station intensity of a buyer MNO required to achieve a given quality-of-service. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possible category as the paper deals with the strategy of a buyer MNO on choosing how many and which MNOs to buy the infrastructure from. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is another possible category as the paper uses techniques from stochastic geometry to find the coverage probability of the infrastructure sharing system and analyzes the power consumption of the network.
